-- Tanzania Lawmakers Elect First Female Speaker of Parliament, News Reports
-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 2010-11-12T06:39:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-12/tanzania-lawmakers-elect-first-female-speaker-of-parliament-news-reports.html
Tanzanian  lawmakers elected the East
African nation’s first female speaker of parliament, Anna
Semamba Makinda, the  Daily News  reported, citing  John Chiligati ,
the ruling Chama cha Mapinduzi party’s secretary for ideology
and publicity.  Makinda, 61, who served as a legislator for 35 years with
the CCM, was formerly the deputy speaker of the house, the
state-run, Dar es Salaam-based newspaper said today. She
defeated two rival female candidates, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Sarah McGregor  in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 